OL,6,FThe report found: "The review
OL,7,Fidentifies a series of decisions, some
OL,8,Fof which were taken in isolation,
OL,9,Fwhich all compounded together and
OL,10,Finadvertently increased risk."
OL,12,FIn total, 5,073 officers and staff
OL,13,Fwere not properly vetted, of whom
OL,14,F4,528 had no Special Branch vetting
OL,15,Fchecks, 431 had no Ministry of Defence
OL,16,F(MoD) checks, and 114 had a vetting
OL,17,Frefusal overturned by a Met internal
OL,18,Fpanel.
OL,20,FAnother 3,338 who were due for vetting
OL,21,Frenewal had only limited checks.
