OL,6,FThe Met estimates that around 1,200
OL,7,Fpeople who joined the force may have
OL,8,Fhad their vetting refused under normal
OL,9,Fpractices, out of around 27,300
OL,10,Fapplications.
OL,12,FSeparately, 17,355 officers and staff
OL,13,Fdid not have their references properly
OL,14,Fchecked, if at all, between 2018 and
OL,15,FApril 2022.
OL,17,FThe Met has not checked each of these
OL,18,Ffiles, but estimates that around 250
OL,19,Fwould not have got a job if their
OL,20,Freferences had been checked.
